[[File:Flag of UNESCO.svg|250px|right]]
The '''International Day for Monuments and Sites''' also known as '''World Heritage Day''' is an [[international observance]] held on [[18 April]] each year around the world with different types of activities, including visits to monuments and [[cultural heritage|heritage sites]], conferences, round tables and newspaper articles. Each year has a theme, for example [[sustainable tourism]] in 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.icomos.org/en/focus/18-april-international-day-for-monuments-and-sites|title=18 April - International Day for Monuments and Sites - International Council on Monuments and Sites|first=Gaia|last=Jungeblodt|website=www.icomos.org}}</ref>

== History ==
The International Day for Monuments and Sites was proposed by the [[International Council on Monuments and Sites]] (ICOMOS) on 18 April 1982 and approved by the General Assembly of [[UNESCO]] in 1983. The aim is to promote [[awareness]] about the [[cultural diversity|diversity]] of [[cultural heritage]] of humanity, their [[vulnerability]] and the efforts required for their protection and [[Conservation-restoration of cultural heritage|conservation]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.icomos.org/en/focus/18-april-international-day-for-monuments-and-sites/18-april-history|title=18 April - History - International Council on Monuments and Sites|first=Lucile|last=Smirnov|website=www.icomos.org}}</ref>

